# Test Cases for Real-Time Message Sync Bug

## Bug Summary
Messages sent via WhatsApp appear in chat view but not in conversation list preview, indicating a sync issue between real-time updates and UI state management.

## Test Cases

### 1. New WhatsApp Message Flow
| Scenario | Input | Expected Output | Edge Case |
|----------|-------|-----------------|-----------|
| Tenant A receives new message from unknown contact | WhatsApp message from +972501234567 | 1. Chat view shows new message<br>2. Conversation list shows new conversation with preview<br>3. Contact name shows as phone number | Message arrives while user is on different tenant page |
| Tenant A receives new message from existing contact | WhatsApp message from known contact | 1. Chat view shows new message<br>2. Conversation list updates timestamp<br>3. Preview shows latest message snippet | Contact has unread messages from previous session |
| Tenant B receives message while viewing Tenant A's chat | Cross-tenant message arrival | Tenant A's UI unchanged, Tenant B's UI updates via real-time | Verify no tenant data leakage |

### 2. Race Condition Simulation
