## Edge Cases to Test

### 1. Timing & Race Conditions
1. **Rapid consecutive messages** (3+ within 500ms) - UI should batch updates
2. **Message arrives during tab switch** - Should update both old and new tab
3. **Slow network + real-time** - Real-time should not overwrite stale fetch data
4. **Browser tab backgrounded** - Real-time should pause/resume correctly

### 2. Data Integrity
1. **Duplicate message IDs** (Baileys bug) - Should deduplicate based on message ID
2. **Malformed message content** (empty, null, very long) - Should handle gracefully
3. **Hebrew RTL with emojis** - Should preserve text direction
4. **Media messages without content** - Should show fallback preview

### 3. Multi-Tenant Scenarios
1. **User belongs to multiple tenants** - Real-time should only update current tenant
2. **Tenant switch during message arrival** - Old tenant should not show new message
3. **Session expired** - Should show auth error, not blank screen

